machine /məˈʃiːn/

(machining,machined,machines) 

1. N-COUNT A machine is a piece of equipment that uses electricity or an engine in order to do a particular kind of work. 机器 [also 'by' N] 

例： I put the coin in the machine and pulled the lever. 我把硬币投进机器，然后拉了控制杆。 

2. N-COUNT You can use machine to refer to a large and well-controlled system or organization. 机构 

例： ...Nazi Germany's military machine. …纳粹德国的军事机构。 

3.  →  see also vending machine 

4. V-T If you machine something, you make it or work on it using a machine. 用机器制造; 用机器加工 [usu passive] 

例： The material is machined in a factory. 该材料在一家工厂用机器加工而成。 

例： ...machined brass zinc alloy gears. …机器加工的黄铜锌合金齿轮。

